What was vendored
-----------------
Only the test cases for the five ACT rules that can reach this pipeline are
included (see the feasibility report). For each rule, ALL published examples
(passed / failed / inapplicable) are vendored, so the set is the complete rule
set and not a favorable subset:

  Link in context is descriptive   (ruleId 5effbb)  18 cases
  Link is descriptive              (ruleId aizyf1)  12 cases
  Form field label is descriptive  (ruleId cc0f0a)  14 cases
  Heading is descriptive           (ruleId b49b2e)  17 cases
  HTML page title is descriptive   (ruleId c4a8a4)   6 cases

  testcases.json : the full published export (all 1134 cases), kept intact.
  html/          : the 67 referenced HTML files for the five rules above.

How this copy is pinned (freeze)
--------------------------------
The published export carries no version field of its own, so the freeze is by
content hash, recorded in `checksums.sha256` (verify with
`shasum -a 256 -c checksums.sha256` from this directory):

  testcases.json  sha256: a805d865d61ae2418e56a6a9d303fe60c85089c792b897eb9472ea5513156293
  html/*.html     sha256: one line per file in checksums.sha256

  Fetched:        2026-07-14
  Freeze id:      act-gold@a805d865   (first 8 hex of the testcases.json sha256)

Note on `testcaseId`: ACT assigns each case a stable SHA-1 identifier
(`testcaseId`), which we carry through as the case identity. It is NOT the SHA-1
of the published HTML bytes fetched here (ACT hashes a source form), so integrity
of this vendored copy is guaranteed by our own sha256 checksums above, not by
recomputing `testcaseId`.

The benchmark runner reads THIS vendored copy only, never the live URL.
